      • Region

        public Region(java.util.List<PointIF> boundaryPoints)
        Creates a simple 'Region' object with one 'Face' without holes by passing a list of points which define the outer boundary. The points of the passed list are connected in the order of their occurrence in the list, whereby the last point of the list is connected with the first.
        Parameters:
        boundaryPoints - - List of points of the boundary
